23/01/2003
PRISTINA, Kosovo, Yugoslavia -- An anti-tank missile slammed into a regional police centre in Pec on Wednesday (22 January), causing some damage but no injuries. A UN spokesman said the rocket hit the second floor of the building and was apparently fired from close range. Police have made no arrests.
In other news, a prominent Serb political leader from Mitrovica was seriously injured in a car accident Wednesday in Serbia. Marko Jaksic's car struck two other vehicles that had collided moments earlier. (AP, AFP - 22/01/03)
